        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 22 at 6:27PM CDT until April 22 at 7:15PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Armstrong County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southeastern Carson County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southwestern Gray County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Northern Donley County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 715 PM CDT.

* At 627 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 5 miles southwest
of Goodnight, or 10 miles southeast of Claude, moving northeast at
30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and half dollar size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
Hail damage to vehicles is expected.

* Locations impacted include...
Howardwick, Groom, Greenbelt Lake, and Goodnight.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
